author: Min Zeng
title: U.S. Government Bonds Hit by China’s Rate Cuts
text:
Investors flocked out of U.S. government bonds Friday after China cut interest rates to support the slowing economy.
China’s announcement of fresh monetary stimulus boosted investors’ appetites for riskier assets and sapped demand for haven debt. European and U.S. stocks strengthened.
